column13: One way to improve the counseling appointment experience would be to allow a little more time for each session, especially during peak times in the semester. Sometimes appointments can feel a bit rushed, and having more time would help students feel fully heard and supported. It would also be helpful if counselors had more availability or flexible scheduling options, like earlier or later hours or virtual appointments, for those of us with tight class or work schedules. Overall, the counselors are knowledgeable and kind—it would just be great to have a bit more time and flexibility to really dive into our academic and personal goals.

This means that EOPS Students are able to register for classes before other student groups., I understand that the classes I need for the following semester are not guaranteed if I don't register on my priority enrollment date.
column23: Overall, the front office staff has been helpful, but there are a few ways the experience could be even better. Sometimes the wait times can be long, especially during busy periods, so having a more efficient check-in process or offering more online options could help. Also, making sure all staff members are consistently friendly and approachable goes a long way in creating a welcoming environment. Clearer communication about appointment scheduling, deadlines, and required documents would also make things smoother for students. I appreciate the work the staff does and think these small changes could make a big difference.
column24: Yes, EOPS services definitely helped me succeed this semester. The counseling appointments were incredibly valuable—they helped me stay on track academically and made it easier to plan my schedule and meet important deadlines. The priority registration benefit was also a huge help in securing the classes I needed. On top of that, the book voucher relieved a lot of financial stress and allowed me to focus more on my studies. I really appreciated the consistent support and communication from the EOPS staff—they made me feel seen and supported throughout the semester.
column25: Unfortunately, I didn’t feel the full benefit of EOPS services this semester. I think more regular check-ins or reminders about available resources would be helpful, especially during busy times in the semester. Sometimes I wasn’t sure how to access certain benefits like the book voucher or when to schedule counseling appointments. Clearer communication and more outreach could help students take full advantage of everything EOPS has to offer. I do appreciate the support that's available—I just think a few small improvements could make the services even more accessible and effective.
column27: I’m currently seeking support in a few key areas to help me succeed at SWC. Academic advising would be extremely helpful to ensure I’m on track with my major and transfer goals. I’d also benefit from career counseling to explore options related to my field of interest and gain clarity on possible career paths. Additionally, access to tutoring services and workshops to strengthen my study skills would make a big difference in helping me stay on top of my coursework. Finally, I’m interested in learning more about student organizations and campus involvement opportunities to build connections and enrich my college experience.

column12: Creating or updating my semester by semester
column13:
During the first appointment the interest of the student should be defined, even if the student is not sure what path to take. 

At the second appointment questions of possible interest for the student should be presented; so the student is appealed to dig into the student's own curiosity while having an informed opinion from the counselor.

This way the student is not limited to what he or she expects from the pathway planned, instead having another perspective that may call the attention of growth, development and/or purpose of the student.

column23: I would like to be able to schedule appointments further in advance. For example, if I need an appointment in three weeks, it should be possible to book it with that much notice. In my case, I was told that I couldn’t schedule so early, and when I came back later, there were no more available spots. This affected me because I missed the opportunity to receive the rewards for being one of the first to attend my appointments, all because I wasn’t allowed to schedule in advance.
column24: Yes, EOPS services helped me this semester. However, what would have helped me even more is having a bit more credit available for school supplies. I would also appreciate being advised or referred to a place where I can work in a field related to what I’m studying, so I can gain experience in the career I want to pursue. Additionally, having more scholarships or financial resources would help me stay focused on my education without being overwhelmed by fixed expenses like housing and my car. Access to scholarships that could help cover those costs would make a big difference for me.
column25: Yes, EOPS services have helped me, but I would like to receive more support through scholarships to better cover my needs without neglecting my studies. My main needs are housing expenses, getting a car (since I don’t currently have one and really need it), and overall support so I can dedicate myself full-time to school. This would help improve my academic performance and allow me to reach my goals.
column26: Housing Needs, Transportation Needs, Academic Support/Study Skills, Technology, Employment, Financial Wellness
column27:
My most urgent needs are related to housing. I need support to reduce my rent costs because that expense is very high, and I currently live alone in Chula Vista. I’m barely able to cover it, and I fear that soon I won’t be able to continue my studies because I’ll need to work more to afford my living expenses.
Additionally, I don’t have a car, and I need one to get around more efficiently. I also need more financial support in general to help cover basic expenses.
I truly want to achieve my academic goals, but it’s becoming very difficult without the proper support. If I could receive a scholarship or other types of assistance to help with these needs, I could dedicate myself 100% to school and perform well enough to reach my goals.
